for integration by parts,

00:00:29.590 --> 00:00:36.200 align:middle line:84%
it was that if I have two
continuously differentiable

00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:56.670 align:middle line:84%
functions, then I can shift the
burden of taking a derivative.

00:00:56.670 --> 00:01:03.330 align:middle line:84%
F prime times g integrate
is equal to f of b, g of b,

00:01:03.330 --> 00:01:13.380 align:middle line:84%
