the interval from a to b of g

00:01:13.380 --> 00:01:15.810 align:middle line:90%
prime f.

00:01:15.810 --> 00:01:21.540 align:middle line:84%
So I can shift that
derivative over from f to g.

00:01:21.540 --> 00:01:27.960 align:middle line:84%
And this is apart from
the triangle inequality,

00:01:27.960 --> 00:01:34.110 align:middle line:84%
probably one of the most
useful theorems that comes out

00:01:34.110 --> 00:01:36.070 align:middle line:84%
of calculus other than
the fundamental theorem

00:01:36.070 --> 00:01:36.570 align:middle line:90%
